AREA Partnership Buys $215 Million of Defaulted Apartment Loans

-- B y   D a v i d   M .   L e v i t t
-- 
2011-09-15T20:36:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/area-partnership-buys-215-million-of-defaulted-apartment-loans.html
AREA Property Partners LP, a New
York-based real estate fund manager, acquired $215 million of
defaulted loans on 17 apartment complexes.  AREA, co-founded by Chairman  William Mack , bought the loans
with McDowell Properties, a San Francisco-based investment firm
with 19,252 apartment units, according to an e-mailed statement
today. The debt was purchased at a 40 percent discount to face
value, AREA said.  The portfolio, which totals 4,733 units, consists of seven
properties in Austin,  Texas ; three in Dallas; three in Tulsa,
Oklahoma; two in Phoenix; and one each in Tampa and
Jacksonville, Florida.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David M. Levitt in New York at 
 dlevitt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kara Wetzel at 
 kwetzel@bloomberg.net  